The article discusses the 40th anniversary of the Iranian hostage crisis, in which Iranian militants stormed the United States Embassy in Tehran and held more than 50 Americans hostage for 444 days. The article states that the Iranian regime continues to target innocent civilians as pawns in its failed foreign relations. The United States will continue to impose crippling sanctions until Iran changes its hostile behavior. The article calls on the Iranian regime to prioritize the Iranian people and choose peace instead of engaging in terrorism, hostage-taking, assassinations, sabotage, maritime hijacking, and attacks on global oil markets. The United States supports the Iranian people and seeks peace.